dtc_dupl_early <- function(dts, vars, groupby, dtc, ...) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    
                    
                      
  # dots are for ordering variables

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    
                    
                      
  ### Subset to only records without missing DTC

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    19x
                    
                      
  mydf <- dts[!is_sas_na(dts[[dtc]]) & !is_sas_na(dts[["VISIT"]]) & !is_sas_na(dts[["VISITNUM"]]) & substr(dts[["VISIT"]], 1, 5) != "UNSCH", vars]

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    
                    
                      
  ### Subset no duplicated records

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    19x
                    
                      
  mydf1 <- mydf[!duplicated(mydf[, vars]), ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    
                    
                      
  ### Sort by

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    19x

                    171
                    19x
                    
                      
  mydf2 <- mydf1[eval(parse(text = ord)), ]

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    173
                    
                    
                      
  ### Add Vis_order

                    		
                  

                  

                    174
                    19x
                    
                      
  splitter <- mydf2[groupby]

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    19x
                    
                      
  mydf2l <- lapply(split(mydf2, splitter, drop = TRUE), function(x) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    176
                    43x
                    
                      
    row.names(x) <- NULL

                    		
                  

                  

                    177
                    
                    
                      
    # if 1 record then no need for lagging

                    		
                  

                  

                    178
                    43x
                    
                      
    if (identical(nrow(x), as.integer(1))) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    179
                    !
                    
                      
      cbind(x, last.vis.dtc = NA, last.vis = NA, visit.order = 1, stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    
                    
                      
      # if 2 records then just lag using the first record

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    43x
                    
                      
    } else if (identical(nrow(x), as.integer(2))) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    1x
                    
                      
      cbind(x, last.vis.dtc = c(NA, x[1, dtc]), last.vis = c(NA, x[1, "VISIT"]), visit.order = seq(1, nrow(x)), stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    
                    
                      
      # if more than 2 records then lag and create as many records as in original

                    		
                  

                  

                    184
                    
                    
                      
    } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    185
                    42x
                    
                      
      cbind(x, last.vis.dtc = c(NA, x[2:nrow(x) - 1, dtc]), last.vis = c(NA, x[2:nrow(x) - 1, "VISIT"]), visit.order = seq(1, nrow(x)), stringsAsFactors = FALSE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    186
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    187
                    
                    
                      
  })

                    		
                  

                  

                    188
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    189
                    
                    
                      
  # need to stack all chunks together

                    		
                  

                  

                    190
                    19x
                    
                      
  mydf2 <- Reduce(rbind, mydf2l)

                    		
                  

                  

                    191
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    192
                    19x
                    
                      
  mydf2$check.flag <- ifelse(mydf2$visit.order != 1 & mydf2$last.vis.dtc == mydf2[[dtc]], "Duplicated",

                    !
                    
                      
                                      get(var_name)

                    		
                  

                  

                    309
                    
                    
                      
               )

                    		
                  

                  

                    310
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    311

  return(dt)

report_to_xlsx = function(res,outfile){

                    		
                  

                  

                    352
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    353
                    
                    
                      
  # prepare summary page

                    		
                  

                  

                    354
                    
                    
                      
  # pull columns (xls_title, pdf_title, nrec, notes) from the list and create a summary data frame

                    		
                  

                  

                    355
                    !
                    
                      
  summary_cols<-lapply(res,'[', c("xls_title","pdf_title","nrec","notes","pdf_subtitle"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    356
                    !
                    
                      
  summary_data_0<-as.data.frame(do.call(rbind,summary_cols)) 

                    		
                  

                  

                    357
                    !
                    
                      
  summary_data = summary_data_0 %>% 

                    		
                  

                  

                    358
                    !
                    
                      
    mutate(version="") %>% select(-any_of("pdf_subtitle"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    359
                    !
                    
                      
  summary_data[,"nrec"]<-as.numeric(summary_data[,"nrec"])

                    		
                  

                  

                    360
                    !
                    
                      
  summary_data[1,"version"]<-nickname

                    		
                  

                  

                    361
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    362
                    
                    
                      
  # assign column names

                    		
                  

                  

                    363
                    !
                    
                      
  colnames(summary_data)<-c("Data check (Tab name)",

                    		
                  

                  

                    364
                    !
                    
                      
                            "Description", 

                    		
                  

                  

                    365
                    !
                    
                      
                            "N of Failed records", 

                    		
                  

                  

                    366
                    !
                    
                      
                            "Notes",

                    		
                  

                  

                    367
                    !
                    
                      
                            paste0("sdtmchecks v.",packageDescription("sdtmchecks")[["Version"]])

                    		
                  

                  

                    368
                    
                    
                      
  )

                    		
                  

                  

                    369
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    370
                    
                    
                      
  # create workbook

                    		
                  

                  

                    371
                    !
                    
                      
  wb<-createWorkbook()

                    		
                  

                  

                    372
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    373
                    
                    
                      
  # add some formatting to summary page

                    		
                  

                  

                    374
                    !
                    
                      
  addWorksheet(wb, "Summary results")

                    		
                  

                  

                    375
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    376
                    !
                    
                      
  setColWidths(wb, "Summary results", cols=1, widths=30)

                    		
                  

                  

                    377
                    !
                    
                      
  setColWidths(wb, "Summary results", cols=2, widths=65)

                    		
                  

                  

                    378
                    !
                    
                      
  setColWidths(wb, "Summary results", cols=3, widths=20)

                    		
                  

                  

                    379
                    !
                    
                      
  setColWidths(wb, "Summary results", cols=4, widths=35)

                    		
                  

                  

                    380
                    !
                    
                      
  setColWidths(wb, "Summary results", cols=5, widths=25)

                    		
                  

                  

                    381
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    382
                    !
                    
                      
  addFilter(wb, "Summary results", cols=1:ncol(summary_data), rows=1 )

                    		
                  

                  

                    383
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    384
                    
                    
                      
  # write summary data on the 1st page of XLS file

                    		
                  

                  

                    385
                    !
                    
                      
  writeData(wb, "Summary results", as.data.frame(summary_data), startRow = 1, startCol = 1, headerStyle=createStyle(textDecoration = "bold"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    386
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    387
                    
                    
                      
  # Highlight the rows with problematic queries ( i.e. have non-missing comments at column D)

                    		
                  

                  

                    388
                    !
                    
                      
  redStyle<-createStyle(fontColour = "#9C0006", bgFill = "#FFC7CE")

                    		
                  

                  

                    389
                    !
                    
                      
  orangeStyle<-createStyle(fontColour = "#000000", bgFill = "#fac966")

                    		
                  

                  

                    390
                    !
                    
                      
  boldnickname<-createStyle(textDecoration = "bold")

                    		
                  

                  

                    391
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    392
                    !
                    
                      
  conditionalFormatting(wb, "Summary results", cols=1:4 ,  rows=1:nrow(summary_data)+1, rule='$D2!=" "', style=redStyle)

                    		
                  

                  

                    393
                    !
                    
                      
  conditionalFormatting(wb, "Summary results", cols=2:4 ,  rows=1:nrow(summary_data)+1, rule='$C2>0', style=orangeStyle)

                    		
                  

                  

                    394
                    !
                    
                      
  conditionalFormatting(wb, "Summary results", cols=1 ,  rows=1:nrow(summary_data)+1, rule='$C2>0', style=orangeStyle)

                    		
                  

                  

                    395
                    !
                    
                      
  conditionalFormatting(wb, "Summary results", cols=5 ,  rows=2, rule='$E2!=""', style=boldnickname)

                    		
                  

                  

                    396
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    397
                    
                    
                      
  # Add comments with PDF subtitles to summary results page

                    		
                  

                  

                    398
                    !
                    
                      
  for(i in 1:nrow(summary_data_0)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    399
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    400
                    !
                    
                      
    writeComment(wb, "Summary results", col=2, row=i+1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    401
                    !
                    
                      
                 comment=createComment(

                    		
                  

                  

                    402
                    !
                    
                      
                   unlist(summary_data_0[i,"pdf_subtitle"]),

                    		
                  

                  

                    403
                    !
                    
                      
                   author = "sdtmchecks",

                    		
                  

                  

                    404
                    !
                    
                      
                   visible = FALSE,

                    		
                  

                  

                    405
                    !
                    
                      
                   width = 2,

                    		
                  

                  

                    406
                    !
                    
                      
                   height = 4

                    		
                  

                  

                    407
                    
                    
                      
                 ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    408
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    409
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    410
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    411
                    
                    
                      
  #loop through the data checks results and write them into separated sheet in xls file.

                    		
                  

                  

                    412
                    !
                    
                      
  for (i in 1:length(res)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    413
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    414
                    
                    
                      
    # do not create xls sheet for data checks with 0 results

                    		
                  

                  

                    415
                    !
                    
                      
    if(res[[i]]$nrec != 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    416
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    417
                    !
                    
                      
      addWorksheet(wb, res[[i]]$xls_title)

                    		
                  

                  

                    418
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    419
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    420
                    
                    
                      
      # Begin writing individual xls tab at row 2.

                    		
                  

                  

                    421
                    
                    
                      
      # Row=1 will be used to create a HYPERLINK back to 'Summary results' sheet.

                    		
                  

                  

                    422
                    
                    
                      
      # writeData(wb, res[[i]]$xls_title, as.data.frame(res[[i]]$data), startRow = 2, startCol = 1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    423
                    !
                    
                      
      writeData(wb, res[[i]]$xls_title, as.data.frame(res[[i]]$data), startRow = 1, startCol = 1)

                    		
                  

                  

                    424
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    425
                    
                    
                      
      # create a HYPERLINK between a row on 'Summary results' sheet and individual tab

                    		
                  

                  

                    426
                    
                    
                      
      # need to have i+1 because the 1st row on 'Summary results' sheet has column names

                    		
                  

                  

                    427
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    428
                    
                    
                      
      # writeFormula(wb, sheet="Summary results", startRow=i+1, startCol=1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    429
                    
                    
                      
      #              x=makeHyperlinkString(sheet=res[[i]]$xls_title, row=1, col=1, text=res[[i]]$xls_title ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    430
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    431
                    !
                    
                      
      writeData(wb, sheet="Summary results", startRow=i+1, startCol=1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    432
                    !
                    
                      
                x=res[[i]]$xls_title )

                    		
                  

                  

                    433
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    434
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    435
                    
                    
                      
      # create a HYPERLINK between an individual tab and the row on 'Summary results' sheet

                    		
                  

                  

                    436
                    
                    
                      
      # need to have i+1 because the 1st row on 'Summary results' sheet has column names

                    		
                  

                  

                    437
                    
                    
                      
      # writeFormula(wb, sheet=res[[i]]$xls_title, startRow=1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    438
                    
                    
                      
      #              x=makeHyperlinkString(sheet="Summary results", row=i+1, col=5, text="Link to Summary Tab" ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    439
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    440
                    
                    
                      
      # Add comments with PDF sub titles to each individual page

                    		
                  

                  

                    441
                    !
                    
                      
      writeComment(wb, res[[i]]$xls_title, col=1, row=1,

                    		
                  

                  

                    442
                    !
                    
                      
                   comment=createComment(

                    		
                  

                  

                    443
                    !
                    
                      
                     unlist(summary_data_0[i,"pdf_subtitle"]),

                    		
                  

                  

                    444
                    !
                    
                      
                     author = "sdtmchecks",

                    		
                  

                  

                    445
                    !
                    
                      
                     visible = FALSE,

                    		
                  

                  

                    446
                    !
                    
                      
                     width = 2,

                    		
                  

                  

                    447
                    !
                    
                      
                     height = 4

                    		
                  

                  

                    448
                    
                    
                      
                   ))

                    		
                  

                  

                    449
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    450
                    
                    
                      
      

                    		
                  

                  

                    451
                    
                    
                      
    } # end of if

                    		
                  

                  

                    452
                    
                    
                      
  } # end of loop

                    		
                  

                  

                    453
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    454
                    !
                    
                      
  saveWorkbook(wb, file = outfile, overwrite = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    455
                    !
                    
                      
  return(invisible())

                    		
                  

                  

                    456
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    457
                    
                    
                      
}

create_R_script <- function(metads=sdtmchecksmeta, file="sdtmchecks_run_all.R") {

                    		
                  

                  

                    504
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    505
                    !
                    
                      
  filterchecks <- metads %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    506
                    !
                    
                      
    mutate(

                    		
                  

                  

                    507
                    !
                    
                      
      n=row_number(),

                    		
                  

                  

                    508
                    !
                    
                      
      check_args = paste0(check, '(', fxn_in, ')',ifelse(n!=nrow(metads),",",""))

                    		
                  

                  

                    509
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    510
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    511
                    !
                    
                      
  write_this <-

                    		
                  

                  

                    512
                    !
                    
                      
    c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    513
                    !
                    
                      
      "# load packages",

                    		
                  

                  

                    514
                    !
                    
                      
      "library(sdtmchecks)",

                    		
                  

                  

                    515
                    !
                    
                      
      "library(dplyr)",

                    		
                  

                  

                    516
                    
                    
                      
      "",

                    		
                  

                  

                    517
                    !
                    
                      
      "# Read your SDTM Domains, e.g.:",

                    		
                  

                  

                    518
                    !
                    
                      
      "# dm = haven::read_sas('path/to/sdtms/dm.sas7bdat')",

#' @title Create list from tabs of spreadsheet (*xlsx)

                    		
                  

                  

                    542

xlsx2list <-function(rptwb, firstrow=1){

                    		
                  

                  

                    575
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    576
                    !
                    
                      
  rptlist <- list()

                    		
                  

                  

                    577
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    578
                    !
                    
                      
  for (rpttab in names(rptwb)){

                    		
                  

                  

                    579
                    !
                    
                      
    print(names(rptwb))

                    		
                  

                  

                    580
                    
                    
                      
    

                    		
                  

                  

                    581
                    
                    
                      
    # startRow is the row with variable/column names

                    		
                  

                  

                    582
                    
                    
                      
    # default is 1

                    		
                  

                  

                    583
                    !
                    
                      
    rptsheet <- openxlsx::read.xlsx(xlsxFile = rptwb, sheet = rpttab, startRow=firstrow, skipEmptyRows = TRUE, detectDates = TRUE)

                    		
                  

                  

                    584
                    !
                    
                      
    rptlist[[rpttab]] <- list(rptsheet)

                    		
                  

                  

                    585
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    586
                    
                    
                      
  

                    		
                  

                  

                    587
                    !
                    
                      
  print("xlsx")

                    		
                  

                  

                    588
                    !
                    
                      
  return(rptlist)

                    		
                  

                  

                    589
                    
                    
                      
}

#' @title Check for Missing EXDOSE.

check_ex_exdose_exoccur <- function(EX, drug=NULL) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    48
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    49
                    6x
                    
                      
    if (EX %lacks_any% c("USUBJID","EXTRT","EXSTDTC","EXDOSE")) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    50
                    1x
                    
                      
      fail(lacks_msg(EX, c("USUBJID","EXTRT","EXSTDTC","EXDOSE")))

                    		
                  

                  

                    51
                    
                    
                      
      # Checks validity of drug name argument

                    		
                  

                  

                    52
                    
                    
                      
    }else{

                    		
                  

                  

                    53
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    54
                    5x
                    
                      
    if (!is.null(drug) && !(drug %in% EX[["EXTRT"]])) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    55
                    !
                    
                      
      fail(msg = "Drug name not found in dataset")

                    		
                  

                  

                    56
                    5x
                    
                      
    }else if (EX %lacks_all% c("EXOCCUR", "VISIT")){

                    		
                  

                  

                    57
                    
                    
                      
      #For DFs *without* EXOCCUR and VISIT variables

                    		
                  

                  

                    58
                    
                    
                      
      # Subsets EX to rows where EXDOSE is missing

                    		
                  

                  

                    59
                    !
                    
                      
      df <- EX %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    60
                    !
                    
                      
        select("USUBJID", "EXTRT", "EXSTDTC", "EXDOSE") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    61
                    !
                    
                      
        filter(is_sas_na(EX[["EXDOSE"]]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    62
                    5x
                    
                      
    }else if (EX %lacks_any% c("EXOCCUR")){

                    		
                  

                  

                    63
                    
                    
                      
      #For DFs *without* EXOCCUR variable but *with* VISIT variable

                    		
                  

                  

                    64
                    
                    
                      
      # Subsets EX to rows where EXDOSE is missing

                    		
                  

                  

                    65
                    1x
                    
                      
      df <- EX %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    66
                    1x
                    
                      
        select("USUBJID", "EXTRT", "VISIT", "EXSTDTC", "EXDOSE") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    67
                    1x
                    
                      
        filter(is_sas_na(EX[["EXDOSE"]]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    68
                    4x
                    
                      
    }else if (EX %lacks_any% c("VISIT")){

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      
      #For DFs *without* VISIT variable but *with* EXOCCUR variable

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      
      # Subsets EX to rows where EXDOSE is missing

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    1x
                    
                      
      df <- EX %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    1x
                    
                      
        select("USUBJID", "EXTRT", "EXSTDTC", "EXOCCUR", "EXDOSE") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    1x
                    
                      
        filter(is_sas_na(EX[["EXDOSE"]]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    
                    
                      
    }else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    75
                    
                    
                      
      # For DFs *with* EXOCCUR and VISIT variables

                    		
                  

                  

                    76
                    
                    
                      
      # Subsets EX to rows where EXOCCUR == "Y" but EXDOSE is missing

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    3x
                    
                      
      df <- EX %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    78
                    3x
                    
                      
        select("USUBJID", "EXTRT", "VISIT", "EXSTDTC", "EXOCCUR", "EXDOSE") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    79
                    3x
                    
                      
        filter(EXOCCUR == "Y" & is_sas_na(EX[["EXDOSE"]]))

                    		
                  

                  

                    80
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    81
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    82
                    5x
                    
                      
  if (!is.null(drug)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    83
                    !
                    
                      
    df <- df %>% filter(EXTRT == drug)

                    		
                  

                  

                    84
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    85
                    
                    
                      
  # Outputs a resulting message depending on whether there are instances with

                    		
                  

                  

                    86
                    
                    
                      
  # EXOCCUR == "Y" and EXDOSE is missing, and whether a drug name is supplied

                    		
                  

                  

                    87
                    5x
                    
                      
  if (nrow(df) != 0 && !is.null(drug)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    88
                    !
                    
                      
    fail(paste0("EX has ", nrow(df), " record(s) with missing EXDOSE when EXOCCUR = 'Y' (or EXOCCUR does not exist) for ", drug,". "), df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    89
                    5x
                    
                      
  } else if (nrow(df) != 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    90
                    1x
                    
                      
    fail(paste0("EX has ", nrow(df), " record(s) with missing EXDOSE when EXOCCUR = 'Y' (or EXOCCUR does not exist). "), df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    91
                    
                    
                      
  } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    92
                    4x
                    
                      
    pass()

                    		
                  

                  

                    93
                    
                    
                      
  }

                    		
                  

                  

                    94
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    95
                    
                    
                      
}

#' @title Check if 4m BCVA test stops too late, too early and has correct total

                    		
                  

                  

                    2
                    
                    
                      
#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' @description This ophthalmology check is for BCVA 4m test. It checks three conditions: <1> BCVA test stops too late,

                    		
                  

                  

                    4
                    
                    
                      
#' meaning that lines were read after number of correct letters is <= 3. <2> BCVA test stops too early, meaning that

                    		
                  

                  

                    5
                    
                    
                      
#' further lines were not read when all numbers of correct letters is > 3. <3> BCVA total score is not correct, meaning

                    		
                  

                  

                    6
                    
                    
                      
#' that the sum of the number of correct at 4 meters doesn't match with what has been recorded in eCRF

                    		
                  

                  

                    7
                    
                    
                      
#' (BCVA Scores eCRF Page - A. Total number correct at 4m). Please note that this check only works with USUBJID, VISIT,

                    		
                  

                  

                    8
                    
                    
                      
#' VISITNUM, OELOC, OELAT combination has unique dates (OEDTC). If your datasets are having situations like 1) unscheduled

                    		
                  

                  

                    9
                    
                    
                      
#' visits happening on different dates or 2) BCVA TOTAL happens on a different date from BCVA row tests, such combinations

                    		
                  

                  

                    10
                    
                    
                      
#' will be removed from check.

                    		
                  

                  

                    11
                    
                    
                      
#' Please note that this check excludes forms BCVA Low Vision Test (BCV5), BCVA Scores (BCV7),

                    		
                  

                  

                    12

                    14

                    16

check_oe_bcva_4m_late_early_tot <- function(OE) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    106
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    107
                    5x
                    
                      
    required_variables <- c(

                    		
                  

                  

                    108
                    5x
                    
                      
        "USUBJID", "OECAT", "OESCAT", "OETSTDTL", "OESTAT", "OERESCAT", "VISIT", "VISITNUM", "OEDTC", "OEDY",

                    		
                  

                  

                    109
                    5x
                    
                      
        "OELOC", "OELAT", "OESTRESN"

                    		
                  

                  

                    110
                    
                    
                      
    )

                    		
                  

                  

                    111
                    5x
                    
                      
    output_variables <- c( "USUBJID", "OETSTDTL", "VISIT", "OEDTC", "OELAT", "OESTRESN")

                    		
                  

                  

                    112
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    113
                    5x
                    
                      
    str_match <- function(x, pattern) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    114
                    8x
                    
                      
        m <- regexpr(pattern, x)

                    		
                  

                  

                    115
                    8x
                    
                      
        regmatches(x, m)

                    		
                  

                  

                    116
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    117
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    118
                    5x
                    
                      
    to_upper_variables <- function(variables) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    119
                    40x
                    
                      
        if(is.character(variables)) return(toupper(variables))

                    		
                  

                  

                    120
                    12x
                    
                      
        else return(variables)

                    		
                  

                  

                    121
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    122
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    123
                    5x
                    
                      
    if(OE %lacks_any% c("OESPID")){

                    		
                  

                  

                    124
                    !
                    
                      
        fail(lacks_msg(OE, c("OESPID")))

                    		
                  

                  

                    125
                    5x
                    
                      
    } else if(OE %>% filter(!grepl("BCV5|BCV7|BCVLL5|BCVAC|BCVACLL", OESPID) &

                    		
                  

                  

                    126
                    5x
                    
                      
                            OECAT == "BEST CORRECTED VISUAL ACUITY" & OETSTDTL == "TESTING DISTANCE: 4M") %>% nrow() == 0){

                    		
                  

                  

                    127
                    !
                    
                      
        pass()

                    		
                  

                  

                    128
                    5x
                    
                      
    } else if (OE %lacks_any% required_variables) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    129
                    1x
                    
                      
        fail(lacks_msg(OE, required_variables))

                    		
                  

                  

                    130
                    
                    
                      
    } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    131
                    
                    
                      
        # preprocessing OE dataset to get the relavant BCVA 4m test data

                    		
                  

                  

                    132
                    
                    
                      
        ### select required variables

                    		
                  

                  

                    133
                    4x
                    
                      
        BCVA_4m <- OE %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    134
                    4x
                    
                      
            select(all_of(required_variables))

                    		
                  

                  

                    135

        # BCVA_4m <- data.frame(lapply(BCVA_4m, to_upper_variables))

                    		
                  

                  

                    137
                    4x
                    
                      
        for(var in required_variables){

                    		
                  

                  

                    138
                    52x
                    
                      
            BCVA_4m[[var]]=to_upper_variables(BCVA_4m[[var]])

                    		
                  

                  

                    139
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    140
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    141
                    
                    
                      
        ### filter on BCVA 4m criteria

                    4x
                    
                      
        BCVA_4m <- BCVA_4m %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    143
                    4x
                    
                      
            filter(

                    		
                  

                  

                    144
                    4x
                    
                      
                OECAT == "BEST CORRECTED VISUAL ACUITY" & OETSTDTL == "TESTING DISTANCE: 4M" &

                    		
                  

                  

                    145
                    4x
                    
                      
                    (!OESTAT %in% c("NOT DONE", "ND")) & OESCAT != "LOW LUMINANCE"

                    		
                  

                  

                    146
                    
                    
                      
            )

                    		
                  

                  

                    147
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    148
                    
                    
                      
        # check if dates are unique for each USUBJID, VISITNUM, OELAT combination, if not, such a combination will be

                    		
                  

                  

                    149
                    
                    
                      
        # removed from the BCVA check including situations like 1) unscheduled visits on different dates, or 2) TOTAL

                    		
                  

                  

                    150
                    
                    
                      
        # date happens on a dfferent date from the BCVA test date

                    		
                  

                  

                    151
                    4x
                    
                      
        nonunique_dates_for_each_sub_visit <- BCVA_4m %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    152
                    4x
                    
                      
            group_by(USUBJID, VISIT, VISITNUM, OELAT) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    153
                    4x
                    
                      
            summarise(num_of_dates = length(unique(OEDTC)), .groups = "drop") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    154
                    4x
                    
                      
            filter(num_of_dates > 1) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    155
                    4x
                    
                      
            ungroup()

                    		
                  

                  

                    156
                    4x
                    
                      
        BCVA_4m <- BCVA_4m %>% left_join(

                    		
                  

                  

                    157
                    4x
                    
                      
            nonunique_dates_for_each_sub_visit,

                    		
                  

                  

                    158
                    4x
                    
                      
            by = c("USUBJID", "VISIT", "VISITNUM", "OELAT")

                    		
                  

                  

                    159
                    
                    
                      
        ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    160
                    4x
                    
                      
            filter(is.na(num_of_dates)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    161
                    4x
                    
                      
            select( - num_of_dates)

                    		
                  

                  

                    162
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    163
                    
                    
                      
        # subcheck 1: if BCVA 4m test stops too late

                    		
                  

                  

                    164
                    4x
                    
                      
        anl1 <- BCVA_4m %>% filter(grepl("ROW \\d+ - SNELLEN \\d+/\\d+", OERESCAT)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    165
                    4x
                    
                      
            mutate(ROW = str_match(OERESCAT, "ROW \\d+"), ROWNUM = as.integer(str_match(ROW, "\\d+"))) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    166
                    4x
                    
                      
            arrange(USUBJID, VISITNUM, OEDTC, OELAT, ROWNUM)

                    		
                  

                  

                    167
                    4x
                    
                      
        late_rows <- anl1 %>% group_by(USUBJID, VISITNUM, OEDTC, OELOC, OELAT) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    168
                    4x
                    
                      
            mutate(LAG_OESTRESN = lag(OESTRESN)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    169
                    4x
                    
                      
            filter(LAG_OESTRESN <= 3) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    170
                    4x
                    
                      
            mutate(MAX_ROW = ifelse(is.na(ROWNUM), NA, min(ROWNUM))) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    171
                    4x
                    
                      
            filter(ROWNUM == MAX_ROW) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    172
                    4x
                    
                      
            ungroup() %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    173
                    4x
                    
                      
            select(USUBJID, VISITNUM, OEDTC, OELOC, OELAT, MAX_ROW)

                    		
                  

                  

                    174
                    4x
                    
                      
        late4m <- anl1 %>% left_join(late_rows, by = c("USUBJID", "VISITNUM", "OEDTC", "OELOC", "OELAT")) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    175
                    4x
                    
                      
            mutate(issue = ifelse(ROWNUM >= MAX_ROW, "BCVA 4m check stops too late", NA)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    176
                    4x
                    
                      
            filter(!is.na(issue) & OESTRESN != 0) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    177
                    4x
                    
                      
            mutate(TOTAL = NA) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    178
                    4x
                    
                      
            select(all_of(output_variables), TOTAL, issue) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    179
                    4x
                    
                      
            unique() #### remove possible duplicates in the result

                    		
                  

                  

                    180
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    181
                    
                    
                      
        # subcheck 2: if BCVA 4m test stops too early

                    		
                  

                  

                    182
                    
                    
                      
        ## anl2 is the same as anl1

                    		
                  

                  

                    183
                    4x
                    
                      
        early4m <- anl1 %>% group_by(USUBJID, VISITNUM, OEDTC, OELOC, OELAT) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    184
                    4x
                    
                      
            mutate(LEAD_OESTRESN = lead(OESTRESN)) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    185
                    4x
                    
                      
            filter(is.na(LEAD_OESTRESN) & OESTRESN > 3 & ROWNUM != 14) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    186
                    4x
                    
                      
            ungroup() %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    187
                    4x
                    
                      
            mutate(

                    		
                  

                  

                    188
                    4x
                    
                      
                TOTAL = NA,

                    		
                  

                  

                    189
                    4x
                    
                      
                issue = "BCVA 4m check stops too early"

                    		
                  

                  

                    190
                    
                    
                      
            ) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    191
                    4x
                    
                      
            select(all_of(output_variables), TOTAL, issue)

                    		
                  

                  

                    192
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    193
                    
                    
                      
        # subcheck 3: if BCVA 4m test has the correct total in eCRF

                    		
                  

                  

                    194
                    
                    
                      
        ## compare total and eCRF, output will include 1) totals in eCRF and calculation don't match

                    		
                  

                  

                    195
                    
                    
                      
        ## 2) total not recorded in eCRF 3) only total in eCRF, not test row/line read

                    		
                  

                  

                    196
                    4x
                    
                      
        anl_total <- BCVA_4m %>% filter(OESCAT %in% c("TOTAL", "NORMAL LIGHTING SCORE"))

                    		
                  

                  

                    197
                    4x
                    
                      
        anl_sum <- anl1 %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    198
                    4x
                    
                      
            group_by(USUBJID, VISIT, VISITNUM, OEDTC, OELOC, OELAT) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    199
                    4x
                    
                      
            summarise(TOTAL = sum(OESTRESN), .groups = "drop") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    200
                    4x
                    
                      
            ungroup()

                    		
                  

                  

                    201
                    4x
                    
                      
        incorrect4m <- anl_total %>% full_join(anl_sum, by = c("USUBJID", "VISIT", "VISITNUM", "OEDTC", "OELOC", "OELAT")) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    202
                    4x
                    
                      
            filter(is.na(TOTAL) | is.na(OESTRESN) | OESTRESN != TOTAL) %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    203
                    4x
                    
                      
            filter(!(OESTRESN == 0 & is.na(TOTAL))) %>% #### remove cases when 4m total is 0 and 4m is not done

                    		
                  

                  

                    204
                    4x
                    
                      
            mutate(issue = "BCVA 4m score incorrect") %>%

                    		
                  

                  

                    205
                    4x
                    
                      
            select(all_of(output_variables), TOTAL, issue)

                    		
                  

                  

                    206
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    207
                    
                    
                      
        ## rbind all three subchecks

                    		
                  

                  

                    208
                    4x
                    
                      
        df <- rbind(late4m, early4m, incorrect4m)

                    		
                  

                  

                    209
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    210
                    4x
                    
                      
        if (nrow(df) != 0) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    211
                    3x
                    
                      
            fail(paste0(nrow(df), " BCVA 4m test record(s) failed with 1) test stops too late 2) test stops too early 3) total incorrect. "), df)

                    		
                  

                  

                    212
                    
                    
                      
        } else {

                    		
                  

                  

                    213
                    1x
                    
                      
            pass()

                    		
                  

                  

                    214
                    
                    
                      
        }

                    		
                  

                  

                    215
                    
                    
                      
    }

                    		
                  

                  

                    216
                    
                    
                      
}

                    		
                  

                
              

            

            

              

                
                  

                    1
                    
                    
                      
#' @title Check that an infusion drug has same start/end exposure dates, also including missing start/end dates

#'

                    		
                  

                  

                    3
                    
                    
                      
#' @description This check identifies that an infusion drug has same EXSTDTC and EXENDTC dateparts.

                    		
                  

                  

                    4

check_ex_infusion_exstdtc_exendtc <- function(EX) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    69
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    70
                    
                    
                      
    ###First check that required variables exist and return a message if they don't

                    		
                  

                  

                    71
                    6x
                    
                      
    if(EX %lacks_any% c("USUBJID", "EXTRT", "EXSTDTC", "EXENDTC", "EXROUTE" )){

                    		
                  

                  

                    72
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    73
                    1x
                    
                      
        fail(lacks_msg(EX, c("USUBJID", "EXTRT", "EXSTDTC", "EXENDTC", "EXROUTE" )))

                    		
                  

                  

                    74
                    
                    
                      

                    		
                  

                  

                    75

                    76
                    5x
                    
                      
        if ("EXOCCUR" %in% names(EX)) {

                    		
                  

                  

                    77
                    3x

                    78

                    79
                    2x
